# AI editors, skills & subagents

- **Canonical project guidelines:** AGENTS.md and CLAUDE.md (in repo root). Prefer updating these over duplicating rules in tool-specific configs.
- **Cursor rules:** This folder (`.cursor/rules/`) adds file-type or topic-specific guidance; they reference AGENTS.md/CLAUDE.md.
- **Skills:** When using Cursor or plugin skills, they should rely on AGENTS.md and CLAUDE.md for project rules. Project root = workspace root.
- **Subagents:** When launching subagents (e.g. mcp_task explore/shell/code-reviewer, exarp-go, Claude custom agents), include in the prompt: project root path and “Canonical guidelines: AGENTS.md and CLAUDE.md in repo root.”
- **Full setup:** See docs/AI_EDITOR_SETUP.md for OpenCode, Claude Code, Cursor, skills, and subagent setup and command parity.
